<task id="002" project="ai-spaarke-insights-engine-r1">
  <metadata>
    <title>D-P17 — IInsightGraph interface + DTOs + stub impl (Cosmos defers to Phase 1.5)</title>
    <status>completed</status>
    <wave>1</wave>
    <estimated-effort>2 hours</estimated-effort>
    <tags>bff-api, interface, graph, dotnet, swap-path-preservation</tags>
    <dependencies></dependencies>
    <parallel-safe>true</parallel-safe>
    <rigor>STANDARD</rigor>
    <d-p>D-P17</d-p>
  </metadata>

  <prompt>
    Define the `IInsightGraph` interface + traversal-spec DTOs in `Sprk.Bff.Api/Services/Insights/Graph/` so Phase 1.5 Cosmos implementation slots in cleanly. Ship a stub `NotImplementedException`-throwing implementation registered in DI so synthesis playbook authors can reason about the abstraction without depending on Cosmos. Preservation #2 from the SPEC integration — cheap to ship now, preserves swap path.
  </prompt>

  <role>Senior .NET developer familiar with named-traversal abstractions and DI stub patterns.</role>

  <goal>
    `IInsightGraph` interface compiled with vertex/edge upsert + named traversals (`FindMattersInvolvingPartyAsync`, `FindConnectedEntitiesAsync` from [design.md §4.2.2](../design.md)). Stub implementation `StubInsightGraph` registered in DI; throws `NotImplementedException("Cosmos NoSqlInsightGraph deferred to Phase 1.5 first deliverable per SPEC §3.3")` on every method. Unit tests verify the stub is reachable via DI.
  </goal>

  <inputs>
    <file purpose="spec">projects/ai-spaarke-insights-engine-r1/SPEC.md (§3.1 D-P17, §3.3 Phase 1.5 first deliverable)</file>
    <file purpose="design">projects/ai-spaarke-insights-engine-r1/design.md (§4.2.2 IInsightGraph C# interface)</file>
    <file purpose="claude">projects/ai-spaarke-insights-engine-r1/CLAUDE.md</file>
  </inputs>

  <constraints>
    <constraint source="ADR-010">DI minimalism — register stub via existing module pattern, no new modules</constraint>
    <constraint source="ADR-013">Zone B placement (Services/Insights/Graph/); no AI internals imports</constraint>
    <constraint source="D-09">Cosmos NoSQL chosen for Phase 1.5; interface must not leak Gremlin syntax</constraint>
  </constraints>

  <knowledge>
    <topic>interface-design, di-stub, swap-path</topic>
    <files>
      <file>docs/adr/ADR-010-di-minimalism.md</file>
    </files>
  </knowledge>

  <steps>
    <step order="1" name="Read design.md §4.2.2">Confirm interface shape</step>
    <step order="2" name="Create folder">Create `Services/Insights/Graph/`</step>
    <step order="3" name="Author DTOs">InsightVertex, InsightEdge, GraphTraversalSpec, GraphTraversalScope, MatterRef</step>
    <step order="4" name="Author interface">IInsightGraph with 6-7 methods (vertex upsert/get/delete, edge upsert/delete, 2 named traversals)</step>
    <step order="5" name="Author stub">StubInsightGraph throwing `NotImplementedException` with clear "Phase 1.5" message + SPEC reference</step>
    <step order="6" name="DI registration">Register `IInsightGraph` -> StubInsightGraph in existing DI module (likely AnalysisServicesModule or new InsightsModule)</step>
    <step order="7" name="Verify discovery">Unit test resolves IInsightGraph via DI; method call throws expected exception</step>
  </steps>

  <tools>
    <tool name="dotnet">Build and run unit tests</tool>
  </tools>

  <outputs>
    <output type="code">src/server/api/Sprk.Bff.Api/Services/Insights/Graph/IInsightGraph.cs</output>
    <output type="code">src/server/api/Sprk.Bff.Api/Services/Insights/Graph/InsightVertex.cs</output>
    <output type="code">src/server/api/Sprk.Bff.Api/Services/Insights/Graph/InsightEdge.cs</output>
    <output type="code">src/server/api/Sprk.Bff.Api/Services/Insights/Graph/StubInsightGraph.cs</output>
    <output type="test">tests/unit/Services/Insights/Graph/StubInsightGraphTests.cs</output>
  </outputs>

  <acceptance-criteria>
    <criterion testable="true">Interface compiles with vertex + edge + 2 named traversal methods</criterion>
    <criterion testable="true">Stub is resolved via `IServiceProvider.GetRequiredService&lt;IInsightGraph&gt;()` in unit test</criterion>
    <criterion testable="true">Calling any stub method throws NotImplementedException with message referencing SPEC §3.3 Phase 1.5</criterion>
    <criterion testable="true">No AI internals imports (grep clean for §3.5.4 forbidden list)</criterion>
  </acceptance-criteria>

  <notes>
    Completed 2026-05-28. Files delivered:
    - `src/server/api/Sprk.Bff.Api/Services/Insights/Graph/IInsightGraph.cs` — interface with 7 methods (3 vertex + 2 edge + 2 named traversals)
    - `src/server/api/Sprk.Bff.Api/Services/Insights/Graph/InsightVertex.cs`, `InsightEdge.cs`, `GraphTraversalSpec.cs` (also contains `GraphTraversalScope` + `MatterRef`) — POCOs with no Gremlin/SQL leaks
    - `src/server/api/Sprk.Bff.Api/Services/Insights/Graph/StubInsightGraph.cs` — every method throws `NotImplementedException("Cosmos NoSqlInsightGraph deferred to Phase 1.5 first deliverable per SPEC §3.3...")` (full message contains both "Phase 1.5" and "SPEC §3.3")
    - `src/server/api/Sprk.Bff.Api/Infrastructure/DI/InsightsModule.cs` — new Zone B feature module per ADR-010 (interface seam justified by D-P17 swap path); registers `IInsightGraph` -> `StubInsightGraph` as singleton
    - `src/server/api/Sprk.Bff.Api/Program.cs` — registration call added after `AddAiChatModule`
    - `tests/unit/Sprk.Bff.Api.Tests/Services/Insights/Graph/StubInsightGraphTests.cs` — 8 xunit tests (DI resolution + 7 method throw assertions)

    Acceptance criteria evidence:
    - Interface compiles with 7 methods: VERIFIED via `dotnet build src/server/api/Sprk.Bff.Api/` — 0 errors, 17 pre-existing warnings (none in new files)
    - Stub resolved via DI: VERIFIED via standalone verifier program (ALL 9 CHECKS PASSED)
    - Every method throws NotImplementedException with "Phase 1.5" + "SPEC §3.3": VERIFIED via verifier (7/7 methods)
    - Zone B §3.5.4 grep clean: VERIFIED (exit code 1, zero matches) against `Services/Insights/Graph/`

    Judgment calls (Step 3 decision):
    1. Created NEW `InsightsModule.cs` rather than extending `AnalysisServicesModule`. Rationale: AnalysisServicesModule is Zone A (freely imports `IOpenAiClient`, `IPlaybookService`, `Microsoft.Extensions.AI` types); the §3.5 facade boundary mandates Zone B Insights code be wired separately so the boundary is visible in DI composition. ADR-010 §Exceptions explicitly permits new interfaces when there's "a true seam" — D-P17 IS a true seam (Phase 1 stub ↔ Phase 1.5 Cosmos impl). Module count cost: +1 of 25 existing modules; offset by Zone B clarity.

    Test runner blocker (pre-existing, unrelated to D-P17):
    - The `Sprk.Bff.Api.Tests` project has 7 pre-existing compile errors from namespace drift in 3 unrelated test files (`EmbeddingMigrationServiceTests`, `AppOnlyDocumentAnalysisJobHandlerTests`, `EmailAnalysisIntegrationTests`). These were last touched months before the Insights Engine work (HEAD: d59f7efd, 1435419e) and are NOT caused by this task's changes. Verified by checking git log -- no commits between origin/master..HEAD modified those test files.
    - To stay on-scope (D-P17 = interface + stub only, STANDARD rigor), I did NOT fix the pre-existing test breakage. Instead I verified the stub's behavior end-to-end via a temporary standalone console verifier referencing the built Sprk.Bff.Api assembly. All 9 verifier checks passed (DI resolution + all 7 stub methods throwing with correct message). The 8-test xunit file (`StubInsightGraphTests.cs`) is shipped as the task deliverable; it will run cleanly once the pre-existing test-project breakage is fixed by whoever owns that area.

    No new ADR violations. No new vulnerabilities. Effort: ~1.5 hours (vs 2 hour estimate).
  </notes>
</task>
